This paper discusses the design of a new network architecture for 5G mobile networks, which involves the integration of software-defined networking (SDN) and cloud computing. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also discusses the use of information theory and control theory in the design, which suggests a possible fit with cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper proposes a new paradigm for 5G networks, which involves the integration of multiple layers, suggesting a possible fit with cs.AR (Hardware Architecture). The paper also discusses the use of programmable components, which suggests a possible fit with cs.SY (Systems and Control). Finally, the paper discusses the challenges of network virtualization and programmability, suggesting a possible fit with cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing).
